  "slug": "crostata-di-nutella",
  "title": "Crostata with chocolate hazelnut filling",
  "subtitle": "Italian shortcrust tart with a hazelnut chocolate filling",
  "excerpt": "A Roman bakery staple: a crumbly pasta frolla tart shell filled with a thick hazelnut chocolate spread and finished with a pastry lattice. The filling is a homemade hazelnut and dark chocolate version, roasted hazelnuts blended with chocolate, cream, and a little butter. Simpler than it sounds, and the flavour is considerably better than a jar-based version.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Crostata is a standard Italian open-pastry tart documented in Italian baking literature from the eighteenth century onward. Pellegrino Artusi, La Scienza in Cucina e l'Arte di Mangiar Bene (1891, freely available at Project Gutenberg IT), describes the crostata format with various fillings. Chocolate and hazelnut combinations in Italian confectionery are documented in Piedmontese and Roman food literature from the nineteenth century, with hazelnut chocolate preparations described in Italian domestic cookery guides published before 1928.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This crostata uses a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "homemade hazelnut chocolate filling",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "Homemade hazelnut chocolate spread",
                  "termId": "cmppnlrwl0000hgv4sdx9vpjz"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " made by roasting and blending hazelnuts with melted dark chocolate and cream. The pasta frolla is the same crumbly Italian pastry used in crostata di ricotta. The filling goes in just thick enough to spread; if it sets too firm before you are ready, warm it gently in a small pan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
